Finally....Truly Gentle Permanent Hair Color.
Color by Robert Craig is the all-new permanent hair color that delivers gorgeous, natural results without a trace of harmful peroxide, ammonia, alcohol or perfume. Plus, built-in conditioners leave the hair silky, luminous and shining with health.













Color by Robert Craigis available in 21 inter- mixable shades. Please refer to our color chart for the available hair color 

choices. Each box comes complete with everything you need to color your 

hair.>>>>>>



Clear can be 

used alone to add shine to the hair or mixed with any of our 21 shades to create a colored gloss. If used alone, mix 

and apply for 15 minutes and enjoy the conditioning and shine benefits with no change in color. Mix with any of our 

21 shades to refresh your color and achieve radiant, natural looking results.






If you would like a complimentary hair color chart and brochure please fill out this form. We will get a hair color chart, order form and brochure out to you. (U.S. residents only) To see the shades on-line, visit our shopping cart.

Robert's Conditioner is highly recommended on Naturallycurly.com - the top web site for curly hair. The hair color is also discussed at length in the hair color section of their discussion boards. Check it out. These are some savvy shoppers.   
And this wonderful conditioner is not just for curly hair. Any hair that needs moisture can benefit from its use. Robert refers to this product as a 'hand cream for hair'.





If you are interested in having a hair colorist do your hair color with Color by Robert Craig there is a listing of wonderful salons using our permanent hair color. For more information click here.



Our permanent hair color is now available to salons so if you are a hair colorist interested in working with a new gentle, permanent hair color that you and your clients will adore please contact us by phone for more information and a special offer to give our hair color a try.(800-917-2566). See our color in this issue of Beauty Launchpad.






Our Healthy Hair vitamins are now available in the shopping cart. Since healthy hair starts from the inside out and is so dependant on one's diet these vitamins are sure to give you the best looking hair ever. Combine with our 'no damage' hair color and you can experience a whole new you.
You can read more about this great new product here.


Watch Us on TV




Color by Robert Craig was recently featured on Living in Style televison show. To view the segment click 
here.

We recently attended a Girls Night Out party in New York City and featured our Clear hair color and No More Bad Hair Days Kit. As well as being open to the public, over 150 editors attended and I think a great time was had by all. To read more about the event and see the FOX news report click here.

Color by Robert Craig was recently featured in a news story about safer hair color options on an NBC affiliate. To view the news segment click 
here.


Robert's No More Bad Hair Days Kit was also featured on Telemundo Father's Day "Grooming" segment. To view that click here.





Among many of her talents, Mary Jo Matsumoto writes for SHEKNOWS.com and is also a home hair color user who chose to try color by Robert Craig. Mary Jo wanted to lighten her hair and followed Robert's advise using the Colorfix dye remover and the Color by Robert Craig hair color. You can read about her experience in this article by clicking here.





NYC Food & Mood Magazine featured our No More Bad Hair Days Kit in the beauty column and the kit is also in  New in the Market and The Advice Sisters. Our permanent hair color has also been written about in Aesthetic Trends. See our "in the news" for the articles.



Life & Style Weekly magazine had an article about our Ultra Blonde Highlight kit that can easily be used over our hair color or our color can be used over the highlights. Our Ultra Blonde highlighting kit also appeared in a recent issue of the Houston
Style news magazine. Be Magazine featured the Ultra blonde Highlight kit which is great to use over our hair color or you can use the hair color over the highlights to tone them.







The web site divaVillage has written an article called Hair to Dye for! about our Color by Robert Craig hair color. Check it out 
here.





NW Stylist and Salon Magazine writes in the What's New in the Market section:
Renowned haircolorist, Robert Craig, creator of Color by Robert Craig, a new gentle permanent hair color developed without a trace of harmful agents like peroxide, ammonia, alcohol, perfume or resorcinol offers the perfect solution to maintaining color treated hair, Robert Craig's No More Bad Hair Days Kit.

 see the complete article here



The online magazine, 

